@NODE AM-intr "Introduction"
   The package @{B}AppMenu@{UB} have two programs. Both run only under Release 3 (V39)
and later versions of the AmigaOS. There are versions for Release 2 (V37/38)
in "Workbench_2.x" drawer too.

   The one @{" AppMenuCx " LINK AM-usin} is a commodity that adds menu items to the Workbench's
Tools menu. When a menu item is activated, @{B}AppMenuCx@{UB} starts a command. The
command is started as separate, asynchronous processes. You can also choose
its arguments through icons or file requester.

   All menu items and commands can be free defined with the help of the second
program @{" AppMenu " LINK AM-usin}. This program works like the others preferences programms.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-inst "Installing and running"
   Copy both programs @{" AppMenuCx and AppMenu " LINK AM-usin} in directories you choosed.
Best place first in WBStartup drawer, second in Prefs drawer.

   Two preferences files will be used too (like by system prefs):
"ENV:AppMenu/AppMenu.prefs" and "ENVARC:AppMenu/AppMenu.prefs". You
must create both directories with "MakeDir ENV:AppMenu" and
"MakeDir ENVARC:AppMenu".

   The programs using the language lacalization from release 2.1 of AmigaOS.
If one of the included catalog files is for the selected language, it can be
coped in one of the directories:
   "LOCALE:Catalogs/<name of language>/" or
   "<dir of the program>/Catalogs/<name of language>/".

   Both programs can be started from Workbench or from Shell.

   @{B}AppMenuCx@{UB} is a commodity and uses only one Shell argument or one icon's tool
type: CX_PRIORITY=<number>. Template is CX_PRIORITY/K/N. Default number is 0.
See Workbench handbook about commodities.

   @{B}AppMenu@{UB} have folowing Shell arguments: FROM=<filename>, EDIT, USE, SAVE and
CLIPUNIT=<clip unit num>. Template is FROM,EDIT/S,USE/S,SAVE/S,CLIPUNIT/K/N.
'<filename>' is the preferences file (default "ENVARC:AppMenu/AppMenu.prefs").
Default '<clip unit num>' is 0 (primary clipboard). Use this arguments like in
Workbench's preferences programs.

   @{B}AppMenu@{UB} uses folowing tool types too:

   CLIPUNIT=<clip unit num> see above.

   SAVEICONS=<NO|YES> is used for state of the @{" Create Icons? " LINK AM-crea} menu item.
Default is YES. By Shell start the menu shows NO.

   SCREENFONT=<NO|YES> says if @{B}AppMenu@{UB} should use the preferences Screen Font
instead of "Topaz/8". Default is YES. It's always used, also by Shell start.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-usin "Using"
   @{B}AppMenu@{UB} creates a file with description of the menu items. @{B}AppMenuCx@{UB} needs
it to make items in the Tools menu and to starts the commands.

   @{B}AppMenu's@{UB} window presents a list gadget with its scroller and a string
field below, a separate string field, a cycle gadget and six buttons. It have
a menu too.

   There are folowing gadgets:

                          @{"                    " LINK AM-menu}
                          @{"    '  list    '    " LINK AM-menu}
              Menu Items: @{"    '   of     '    " LINK AM-menu}
                          @{"    'menu items'    " LINK AM-menu}
                          @{"                    " LINK AM-menu}
        @{"  New  " LINK AM-new} @{"  Del  " LINK AM-del}  @{"    'menu item'     " LINK AM-menu}

        Command:            Arg: @{" 'arguments' " LINK AM-argu}

        @{" > " LINK AM-creq} @{"             'command'            " LINK AM-comm}


        @{"   Save   " LINK AM-save}    @{"   Use    " LINK AM-use}    @{"  Cancel  " LINK AM-quit}


   And folowing menu items:

      Project               Edit                  Options
        @{" Open...    'O' " LINK AM-open}      @{" Cut        'X' " LINK AM-cutt}      @{" Create icons? 'I' " LINK AM-crea}
        @{" Save as... 'A' " LINK AM-saas}      @{" Copy       'C' " LINK AM-copy}
        @{" About...   '?' " LINK AM-auth}      @{" Paste      'V' " LINK AM-past}
         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
        @{" Quit       'Q' " LINK AM-quit}      @{" Move Up    'U' " LINK AM-move}
                               @{" Move Down  'D' " LINK AM-move}
                                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                               @{" Last saved 'L' " LINK AM-last}
                               @{" Restore    'R' " LINK AM-rest}

   @{B}AppMenuCx@{UB} has no window, but you can control it like others commodities
with the "Exchange" program. @{B}AppMenuCx@{UB} uses always the newest
"ENV:AppMenu/AppMenu.prefs" file.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-menu "Gadget: Menu Items"
   This listview gadgets show the item list. To change a item just select it.
Now you can update the @{" Command " LINK AM-comm} text. Press Return or Tab key or change @{" Arg " LINK AM-argu}
gadget to activate the string field below the listview gadget. Here you can
modify the item text and press Return to take the item back to the list.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-comm "Gadget: Command"
   Type the command and its arguments you want to execute. Note that you must
specify the full path of the command when you start @{B}AppMenu@{UB} from Workbench.
It knows "C:" path only in this case. You can solve this problem when you add
this line in "S:User-startup": "ASSIGN C: <path_of_the_cmd> <...> ADD".

   The arguments will be added at the end of the command. If it needs them on
the other place, mark it with ' [] ' like by Alias command.

   It's possible to type several files when you separate them with
<Ctrl LCommand J>. All programs will be started synchronous. It's made
internal through the DOS function System() so you can use it by 'Execute
Command ...' or in Shell too.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-creq "Gadget: '>' - Choose command"
   Show file requester. You can choose new text for @{" Command " LINK AM-comm}.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-argu "Gadget: Arg"
   Select if and from where you want arguments to a command. If one of the
string gadgets is active you can press <RCommand G> and <RCommand Shift G>
to select it. The possibilities are:

   None            Execute command without extra arguments.

   Requester       If you activate the item a file requester appears and you
                   can choose a file name as an argument to the command. You
                   can cancel the execution too.

   Icons           The names of selected icons in Workbench (if any) will be
                   arguments.

   Icons/Request   Same as above. If no icon selected as 'Requester'.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-new "Gadget: New"
   Add a new item to the list. Just type a @{" Command " LINK AM-comm} text, choose @{" Arg " LINK AM-argu} and
write a menu item text. To quick add a program just drop its icons in the
@{" Menu Items " LINK AM-menu} gadget. To add a new item befor an existing item in the list
simple select this item first.

   The number of items you can add is limited only by available memory, the
system however creates current only 63 selectable menu items.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-del "Gadget: Del"
   Remove the selected item from the list.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-save "Gadget: Save"
   Save the item list to "ENVARC:AppMenuCx/AppMenu.prefs". Further as @{" Use " LINK AM-use}.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-use "Gadget: Use"
   Save the item list to "ENV:AppMenuCx/AppMenu.prefs" and quit @{B}AppMenu@{UB}.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-quit "Menu: Project/Quit; Gadget: Cancel"
   Quit @{B}AppMenu@{UB}. If the changed items are not saved a requester appears.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-open "Menu: Project/Open..."
   Load new items from a selected file. If the changed items are not saved
a requester appears. You can also drop a file icons in the window (except in
@{" Menu Items " LINK AM-menu} gadget).
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-saas "Menu: Project/Save As..."
   Save the item list to a selected preferences file.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-cutt "Menu: Edit/Cut"
   Copy the text of a item to clip like with @{" Copy " LINK AM-copy} and delete the item from
the list.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-copy "Menu: Edit/Copy"
   Copy the text of a item to clip. It will be all saved in the form:
'<command-text>;<arguments-code><item-text>. So you can delete this item and
add it back to the list at other place with @{" New " LINK AM-new} and @{" Paste " LINK AM-past}. You can use
it in Shell (note ';') too.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-past "Menu: Edit/Paste"
   Change current command with a text from clip. If the text has the form like
in @{" Copy " LINK AM-copy} all will be changed.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-move "Menu: Edit/Move Up, Edit/Move Down"
   Move the selected item in the list by one up or down.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-last "Menu: Edit/Last saved"
   Load the at last with @{" Save " LINK AM-save} saved items.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-rest "Menu: Edit/Restore"
   Undo all changes in the list since the programm starts.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-crea "Menu: Options/Create icons?"
   Says if create an icon for file from @{" Save As ... " LINK AM-saas}.
@ENDNODE
@NODE AM-erro "Error messages"
   The programs can make folowing error messages.

   @{B}AppMenu@{UB}:
    - Could not activate appwindow
         No Paste with icon placed in window. Continuation.
    - Could not open file requester
         Could not open library: asl.library (V37) or not enough memory for
         file requester. Choosed function breaks. Continuation.
    - Could not open window
         Not enough memory for window. Quit.
    - Error coping to Clip
    - Error pasting from Clip
         Could not open Clipboard or an error by read or write. Copy or Paste
         breaks. Continuation.
    - Error loading IFF file <name>
         Error loading file or not enough memory for new preferences. Cont.
    - Error saving IFF file <name>
         Error saving file. Continuation.
    - Invalid resident library
         Version for WB 3.x was started on 2.x or could not open one of the
         libraries: intuition.library (V37), gadtools.library (V37),
         workbench.library (V37), icon.library (V37), iffparse.library (V37).
         Quit.
    - Not enough memory available
         Not anough memory for program or choosed function. In first case
         program quits, in second the funktion breaks.

   @{B}AppMenuCx@{UB}:
    - Command line too long
         Choosed arguments makes the command too long. System set max lenght
         at 512. The command will not be executed.
    - Could not create all menu items
         Not enough memory to create all menu items. Continuation.
    - Could not create CxObject
         Could not make the program to be Commodity. Quit.
    - Could not open file requester
         Could not open library: asl.library (V37) or not enough memory for
         file requester. Choosed function breaks. Continuation.
    - Could not setup notification on file "ENV:AppMenu/AppMenu.prefs"
         Not enough memory or problems with the file. Quit.
    - Error loading IFF file "ENV:AppMenu/AppMenu.prefs"
         Error loading file or not enough memory for new preferences. Quit.
    - Invalid resident library
         Version for WB 3.x was started on 2.x or could not open one of the
         libraries: intuition.library (V37), commodities.library (V37),
         workbench.library (V37), icon.library (V37), iffparse.library (V37).
         Quit.
    - Not enough memory available
         Not anough memory for program or choosed function. In first case
         program quits, in second the funktion breaks.
@ENDNODE
